> Hello! I'm João Marcelo, a software development student with experience in software testing transitioning to the web development area.

> My professional journey began on the factory floor when I took the industrial mechatronics course from 2011 to 2012, but what caught my attention the most at that time was computer programming.

> Today, after more than 10 years working on the factory floor, I decided to invest in this field that fascinated me more than anything during my studies.

> My focus was to learn about web development, and for that, I decided to dedicate as much time as possible to studying Javascript, as it is a technology that can be used both for front-end and back-end.

> In 2020, I had the opportunity to join a web development team as QA, where I could learn more about the technologies used in the market.

> Over the past 4 years, I've had the privilege of starting a fully remote internship, being hired, and being able to share knowledge with new professionals in the field.

